# Day 3 – Linked Services

## ✔ What I Learned
- Linked Service is the "connection" ADF uses to access a data store.
- Without a Linked Service, ADF cannot open or read data from Storage.
- Learned difference between:
  - Blob Storage Linked Service
  - ADLS Gen2 Linked Service

## ✔ What I Created
- Azure Blob Storage (connects to old Blob storage)
- LS_ADLS_Healthcare (connects to new ADLS Gen2 storage)

## ✔ Issues Faced
- ADLS Gen2 linked service error:
  - Caused by storage account not having Hierarchical Namespace.
  - Fixed by creating a new ADLS Gen2 storage account.

## ✔ Why This Matters
Linked services are required before creating datasets or pipelines.
